canonical:
  title: 澄心軒次韻
  author: 金壽童
  language: lzh
  text: 風生珍簟翠紋流竹影波光滿箔秋莫遣渚禽啼夜月樓中宿客動覊愁
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 澄心軒次韻
  author: 金壽童
  language: lzh
  text: 風生珍簟翠紋流。竹影波光滿箔秋。莫遣渚禽啼夜月。樓中宿客動覊愁。
korean:
  title: 징심헌 차운
  author: 김수동
  language: kor
  text: |-
    자리에 바람 나서 푸른 무늬 흐르는 듯
    대 그림자 물결 빛 한 주렴에 가득하구나
    물새 시키어서 달밤에 우지 마오
    누 속에 묵는 객이 시름 절로 나노매라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1460_010_0210&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Following the Rhymes at Cheongsim Pavilion
  author: Kim Su-dong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Wind stirs the precious mat, jade patterns seeming to flow.
    Bamboo shadows and water's gleam fill the entire autumn screen.
    Do not let the river birds cry through the moonlit night—
    A guest lodging in the tower feels wandering sorrow awaken.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Cheongsim Pavilion (澄心軒) was likely a study or retreat space, and this poem follows the rhyme scheme of an earlier poem written about or at this location.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'precious mat' and 'jade patterns' evoke the refined aesthetics of a scholar's retreat, while bamboo remains a traditional symbol of virtue and integrity in East Asian poetry.
